<!--
  Per-FR detail lives in `specs/frs/<id>.md` (post-M18 architecture). This
  section captures concerns that span multiple FRs — anything that would be
  duplicated across feature specs if not pulled out here.

  Examples of what belongs here (drop the ones that don't apply, replace
  bracketed text with project specifics, and add your own):

    - **Authentication scheme:** how users prove identity across every
      feature. e.g., "OIDC with refresh-token rotation; session cookies
      are HttpOnly + SameSite=Lax".
    - **Observability surface:** structured logs, traces, metric naming
      conventions every FR must follow. e.g., "every request emits a span
      with `feature.name` + `tenant.id` attributes".
    - **Accessibility posture:** WCAG level, keyboard-nav requirement,
      screen-reader contract every UI FR inherits.
    - **Tenancy model:** single- vs multi-tenant invariants every data
      access path must respect.

  What does NOT belong here: any requirement scoped to one feature, even
  if cross-cutting in spirit (e.g., "search must support typo-tolerance"
  belongs in `specs/frs/search.md`).
